This paper deals with a scheduling problem, which is a classic topic in computer science. The use of OR-precedence constraints is a specific variation of the problem, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and optimality, which are common themes in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category, as scheduling problems can be modeled as games with strategic interactions.
